<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99752711846025></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99752711846025><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/search.shtml?id=3779&mid=99752711846025>Confirm that spawn is rare but active</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 11th 6:51 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just completed the Kerran Toy quest yesterday on Luclin server.<br><br>I did talk to Nilit Druzlit (Pos 1890, Neg 310) with the following result:<br><br>You say, 'Hail, Nilit Druzlit'<br><br>Nilit Druzlit says 'Eh?  Eh?!  Talk not now!  My [creation] is running wild!  Destroy it for me, please!  If you do you can keep whatever parts you want from it. <br><br>You say, 'What creation'<br><br>Nilit Druzlit says 'Did you kill it yet? What? Bah!  Yes, I made it.  Nilit's clockwork it is. I made it to carry my toys to and from Ak'Anon but now it's gone wild and started attacking people. Please, destroy it! <br><br>However, despite doing this many times it did not seem to make any difference to the spawns in front of Minotaur Caves. Talking to other players I found out that Nilit's Clockwork had been seen about 24 RL hours earlier (shortly before I had got on the previous day) and that they felt it was on a 'strange' cycle. I had already taken to slaughtering everything that moved and carried on in this way. I spent about 4 or 5 hours killing yard trash in front of caves including taking down the Kobold Missionary 3 or 4 times, and witnessing the demise of, or helping take down the Minotaur Hero 3 times. Finally, Nilit's Clockwork (looking the same from a distance as any of the Rogue Clockworks) came strolling up from the south. It was 3AM game time, but I don't know if that was relevant. Not a hard kill for me at level 37 but certainly tougher by quite a way than the Rogue's. Did a minor amount of damage (less than 100 hp I think) with 754AC. Had the Gnomish Tinkered Toy on it which is NO DROP.<br><br>Strolled out of Steamfont a little while later, hitched a ride with a wizard to Toxx and from there to Kerran Isle. Found the Kerran Tseq's (Pos 220, Neg 145 ish), hailed them and passed them the Gnomish Toy, got the Kerran Toy (3AC 2AGI 0.1WT) back in return. Being kids the Kerrans then told me to take a hike as they wanted to play with their new toy (sorry forgot to log the messages).<br><br>Added a total of 5AC when I dropped it in my range slot. Pretty happy with that.<br><br>Sengai Wu &lt;Epic Courage&gt;<br>37th Level Monk<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
